Therefore, the answer is \boxed{6^{\frac{5}{3}} - 1}. **Final Answer** \boxed{6^{\frac{5}{3}} - 1} </think> Given \( T = 8 \), the volume of the cube is \( T - 2 = 8 - 2 = 6 \). The edge length of the cube is the cube root of 6, denoted as \( a = \sqrt[3]{6} \). The surface area of the cube is calculated as: \[ 6 \times a^2 = 6 \times (\sqrt[3]{6})^2 = 6 \times 6^{2/3} = 6^{1 + 2/3} = 6^{5/3} \] The surface area of the cube is one-eighth the surface area of a \( 2 \times 2 \times n \) rectangular prism. Therefore, the surface area of the prism is: \[ 8 \times \text{(surface area of the cube)} = 8 \times 6^{5/3} \] The surface area of the rectangular prism is also calculated as: \[ 2 \times (2 \times 2 + 2 \times n + 2 \times n) = 2 \times (4 + 4n) = 8 + 8n \] Equating the two expressions for the surface area of the prism: \[ 8 + 8n = 8 \times 6^{5/3} \] Dividing both sides by 8: \[ 1 + n = 6^{5/3} \] Solving for \( n \): \[ n = 6^{5/3} - 1 \] Thus, the final answer is: \[ \boxed{6^{\frac{5}{3}} - 1} \]
